notesStmt.note: This working group discussion involves five students preparing a joint project for a university course they all attend. It seems that each student has been assigned a particular function in the working group during their seminar course. S1, for example, appears to be the one who has to organize the group and she also chairs the discussion. S2 takes minutes and therefore works on his laptop during the discussion. S4 is the planner of the project. The participants talk about organizational matters such as who will do which parts of the assignment, when they will send each other their parts to proofread or how many warnings you get before you are kicked out of the group.
